            <compact_paragraph toctree="True"><bullet_list><list_item classes="toctree-l1"><compact_paragraph classes="toctree-l1"><reference anchorname="" internal="True" refuri="getting_source">Getting the source</reference></compact_paragraph></list_item><list_item classes="toctree-l1"><compact_paragraph classes="toctree-l1"><reference anchorname="" internal="True" refuri="introduction_to_the_buildsystem">Introduction to the buildsystem</reference></compact_paragraph></list_item></bullet_list></compact_paragraph>
        </compound>
        <rubric heading-level="2">Building for target platforms</rubric>
        <paragraph>Below you can find instructions for compiling the engine for your specific target platform.
            Note that Godot supports cross-compilation, which means you can compile it for a target platform
            that doesn't match your current platform (say, target Linux while being on Windows). The guides
            will try their best to cover all possible situations.</paragraph>
